law.text:
A rental-purchase agreement shall not contain a provision:
Requiring a confession of judgment;
Requiring a garnishment of wages;
Granting authorization to the lessor of a person acting on the lessor's behalf to enter unlawfully upon the consumer's premises or to commit any breach of the peace in the repossession of goods;
Requiring the consumer to waive any defense, counterclaim or right of action against the lessor or a person acting on the lessor's behalf in collection of payment under the lease or in the repossession of goods; or
Requiring purchase of insurance from the lessor to cover the merchandise.
